        Official Singles Chart on 27/11/2020

        27 November 2020 - 3 December 2020

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (27/11/2020 - 04/12/2020)

        (Negative)

        1) I think just about everybody here (even some of the die-hard Arianators!), are getting tired seeing Positions at #1! Yeah, of course a lead single from a huge global popstar like Ariana Grande was going to top the charts but for five consecutive weeks?! This better not pass Thank U, Next as her longest leader.

        2) I dont know if its a trend in 2020, but I just cant connect with neither Shawns nor JBs music! For the former, if its trying to go for more of a rock edge with his upcoming album honestly, for as much as Im not really all that sold on Wonder, he at least had some real punch there! Instead, he just sounds really boring & unengaged here, with really blocky & flat production that wouldnt even do him any justice anyway. Sure, the content does have a more interesting theme behind it this time, but JB cant really add anything onto that! Like I said, this is really not clicking for me & its so frustrating, because I know both artists have way more talent in them, e.g. Something Big, Theres Nothing Holdin Me Back & If I Cant Have You for Shawn Mendes, along with What Do You Mean?, Sorry & Cold Water for Justin Bieber... to name only a few! Both of them need to go back to those kind of songs & for as mean as it sounds, I actually hope this tanks in order for them to realise that.

        3) Mind you, at least Wonder doesnt have the wailing & incredibly forgettable flow that Whoopty does, so to see absolutely blow up on Spotify & almost crack the Top 10 is truly concerning! Trust me, if I have a strongly negative section, the gain for this would probably be in it.

        4) Ive just given up on Diamonds hitting the Top 10 at this point! Sam Smith, Im so sorry, you deserved way better than this with such an anthem.

        5) Why the heck is Loading back in?! Those trumpets are so bad that I cant focus on anything else to do with the song.

        (Mixed)

        1) I cant remember if Ive said this before, but I actually knew a lot about BTS & even supported some of the native hits before they even touched the UK charts, so its kind of cool that theyre at the point now where they can sell literally tens of thousands of copies, even if it isnt in English! Unfortunately, this one cooled off me a fair bit throughout the week. Sure, I really like the gentle production & the smooth vocals, but it does feel like some of the members sound very strained when they push into their upper range & it wouldnt go off live at all in my opinion! The description of life events has been a key part of what BTS really good songwriters, but this just doesnt land in the same way for me & it sounds more like a track that should be left as a deep-cut. Again, this isnt bad, but dont expect this to have the same kind of longevity that Dynamite had, because I doubt itll even come close to that!

        2) I dont know how it managed it, but Blinding Lights is still here! Dont get me wrong, I still love the song & it didnt even leave my own chart all that long ago, but man, 52 weeks inside the Official Chart is too much for any song. I said it about Dance Monkey & Ill say it again here, but sometimes, youve just got to let a huge smash go for a while before you genuinely realise how awesome it is! Im impressed that it hit this significant milestone, but yeah, we need to drop it for something far newer now (maybe even an upcoming Christmas song?).

        3) So I only heard Plugged In Freestyle for the first time during the chart show the drill-inspired beat was definitely a right fit for Fumez The Engineers flow, but Im not really sure how much hype he brings to this as an MC. Again, after only one listen, thats all I can say on it for now, but overall, while I see the appeal behind this, I dont think its on a solid enough level to stick with me personally.

        4) Magic always seems to happen on the albums chart whenever Michael Ball & Alfie Boe work together! Its not really my particular style of music, but Ill tell you this, its definitely going to get a second week on Christmas week for sure.

        (Positive)

        1) While there wasnt really much action at the very top, I adore seeing Levitating break through into the Top 5! I said that this would be a successful single choice from the day Future Nostalgia was released & exactly eight months later, Im so happy to say that I was right. The DaBaby remix is fire too.

        2) Speaking of Dua okay, I was honestly unsure about how well Prisoner would hold up, but Ill tell you what, Im so glad that its the highest debut of the week! Not only do Dua & MIley have amazing chemistry & charisma in this, but the latter brings back her intensely raw vocals, which the more Im hearing them, the more I believe thats the reason that shes getting a second wind in 2020. The guitar groove & the interpolation on the disco classic Physical (also a Dua reference) are really cool features too! I dont know how thisll get promoted with both Levitating & Midnight Sky both still performing even better, but yeah, I really hope this catches onto the radio early & doesnt get dropped now ahead of the inevitable festive takeover. Awesome collaboration!

        3) One word Christmas! Okay, the insanely huge jump for Mariah is the highlight (especially considering were still not even in December yet!), but I honestly either like or love every other festive song here too, even if the inevitable & ginormous takeover throughout the next month will undoubtedly get a little annoying if its starting this soon, haha.

        4) Finally a EDM song that I recommend before its picked up on airwaves is slowly becoming a real dark horse in the charts! The fact that this summery banger is doing so well on downloads despite the country not having the right weather nor situation for it right now is a really promising sign for dance music in 2020 & it shows how optimistic some music fans are about the future. If it can do the same throughout December, then it might even start 2021 in a better position than it is now!

        5) Netflix & PS5, youve just got a Post Malone tune thats aged amazingly well for me back into the Top 40, so thank you so much! Since it came off ACR this week, it might not even drop away that fast either. This reminds me of far simpler times!

        6) On the other hand, while Im indifferent on Holy & Lemonade finally getting put on ACR this week, it did clear out both Daisy & Put Your Records On, which is certainly a step in the right direction! Im still baffled that the latter two even got this far at all, but hey, at least theyre both a thing of the past now.

        Thanks for reading everyone! Have a good weekend. :)
